3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper introduces a new type of neural network, the deep loopy neural network, which involves a large number of loops and requires a new learning algorithm. This falls under the scope of neural computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The proposed model and learning algorithm can be applied to various social and information networks, such as citation networks and social networks, which makes cs.SI a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not focus on computer vision, the proposed model and learning algorithm can be applied to various graph-based computer vision tasks, such as image segmentation and object recognition, which makes cs.CV a possible sub-category.
